{
  "enabled": false,
  "name": "create-component-story",
  "description": "Create Storybook story file for new React components",
  "when": {
    "type": "fileCreated",
    "patterns": [
      "frontend/components/**/*.tsx"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "A new React component has been created at ${FILE}. Please use Desktop Commander MCP to create a corresponding Storybook story file:\n\n1. Create story file at same location with '.stories.tsx' suffix\n   Example: Button.tsx → Button.stories.tsx\n\n2. Add Storybook story template:\n```typescript\nimport type { Meta, StoryObj } from '@storybook/react';\nimport { [ComponentName] } from './[ComponentName]';\n\nconst meta: Meta<typeof [ComponentName]> = {\n  title: 'Components/[ComponentName]',\n  component: [ComponentName],\n  tags: ['autodocs'],\n  argTypes: {\n    // Add prop controls here\n  },\n};\n\nexport default meta;\ntype Story = StoryObj<typeof [ComponentName]>;\n\nexport const Default: Story = {\n  args: {\n    // Add default props here\n  },\n};\n\nexport const [Variant]: Story = {\n  args: {\n    // Add variant props here\n  },\n};\n```\n\nUse mcp_desktop_commander_mcp_write_file() to create the story file. Replace [ComponentName] with the actual component name. Only create if Storybook is configured in the project."
  },
  "blocking": false
}